1 Secr etary, the Lieutenant Governor, the State Auditor and Inspector
2 and the State Treasurer as members. Any member may appoint and
3 designate a subofficer or employee as his or her proxy for purposes
4 of carrying on the duties of the Commission. The Commission shall
5 have sole, entire and exclusive authority of the disposition for all
6 public records and archives of state officers, departments, boards,
7 commissions, agencies and institutions of this state. The authority
8 herein granted shall not apply to records and archives of political
9 subdivisions of the state; provided, however, Section 305 et seq. of
10 this title shall not apply to the confidential records and files of
11 the Oklahoma Tax Commission which are exempt from all provisions of
12 this act.
13
